  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nNot all variants of api servers store the TLS cert files at /var/run/kubernetes. After the commit acba2cb was merged back in Feb, some variants such as kube-aggregator stores them at 'apiserver.local.config/certificates', but the hard-coded help message still says it will save the keys and certs generated into /var/run/kubernetes.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nEither we refactor the code so the help message prints an accurate location, or we change the help message to make it always true.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n`kube-aggregator --help`\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): at least 1.7 and above\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: N/A\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): N/A\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): N/A\r\n- Install tools: N/A\r\n- Others: N/A\r\n",
